<br>
What I hate most of all are 2 things.  <br>
<br>
1.  People who expect the cleric in the group to lose money on symbols while they are getting cash.  If you are such a cheap bastard you arent willing to pay your share for symbols...well find another group.  Symboling the main tank can help alot, with CHeal, and save the cleric lots of mana, definately worth a few pp.<br>
<br>
Cleric should be paid for every symbol he spends in full, with pp (gems are only worth it in Seb that I have seen).  I dont mind counting the symbols I cast myself to make sure im not ripping off the group either.<br>
<br>
2.  People who &quot;expect&quot; a res.  Ask for one, dont view it as the clerics obligation however.  I dont view it as the druid/wizards obligation to port me.<br>
<br>
The ability to ressurect someone is one of the clerics main spells that gets him into groups.  If he doesnt get into groups he cant do anything worthwhile.  If everyone got a free res whenever they wanted, that would make resing a worthless skill and no need to add a cleric for that.  <br>
<br>
That is why some clerics get annoyed when being asked for a res when they are lfg.  If you want a res, get a cleric.  If you dont think you &quot;need&quot; one, then you obviously dont need a res =p.<br>
