And the 'Clerics can charge for rezzes' line isn't weak?  I've done almost 100 resses for people I don't know, and I've maybe made 1k out of it.  I refuse to hold someone's XP hostage for a few pieces of plat...  Most high level clerics res people whenever time permits as more of a professional courtesy at this point than anything else (and god how my life would be simpler if porters would feel the same way.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :/ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":/"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).   Besides, if someone drags a corpse to me and I just sit there demanding 100p for a res when all I have to do is stand up and clickystick them, that kind of makes me a gimp-ass cleric, now doesn't it?<br>
<br>
&gt;&gt;&gt;I believe in equitable adjustments. No more, no less. As a matter of fact, if I am in an xp group w/a cleric, I estimate we will be there 4 hours, I will give the cleric 5 peridots to cover my share.<br>
<br>
If loot was properly balanced everywhere, that would be fine.  If everyone provided their clerics with Peris, that would be fine.  Fact of the matter is it doesnt happen.  In all the non-guild XP groups Ive had, I *might* have been given 20 Peris total for symbols, and I refuse to make myself a gimp-ass cleric and refuse to symbol people until they fork over some plat because that impedes not only my efficiency, but also the efficiency of the group.  So, most clerics lose money.  Seb is generally accepted as penance for everyplace else clerics get shorted.  Still though, I think your point is more along the lines of not forgetting to compensate chanters, which should be addressed in all groups everybit as much as clerics.<br>
